17 Sec. 5.5. 1. “Cosmetic surgery” means a surgical procedure that:
18 (a) Does not meaningfully promote the proper function of the body;
19 (b) Does not prevent or treat illness or disease; and
20 (c) Is primarily directed at improving or preserving the appearance of a
21 person.
22 2. This term does not include reconstructive surgery when such service is
23 incidental to or follows surgery resulting from the diagnosis, prevention,
24 treatment, cure or relief from a physical, dental, behavioral or substance use
25 disorder, mental health condition, illness, injury or disease.
26 Sec. 6. “Extraordinary collection action” means:
27 1. Selling or transferring, with or without compensation, the medical debt
28 of a consumer to a collection agency;
29 2. Any action that requires a legal or judicial process, including, without
30 limitation, placing a lien, except for a lien on a third party settlement, or
31 commencing a civil action;
32 3. Reporting, furnishing or threatening to report or furnish any
33 information regarding a medical debt to a consumer reporting agency; or
34 4. Garnishing or threatening to garnish the wages of a consumer.
35 Sec. 7. “Financial assistance policy” means a written financial assistance
36 policy of a health care entity which the entity is required to maintain pursuant to
37 section 501(r) of the Internal Revenue Code, 26 U.S.C. § 501(r) or the provisions
38 of chapter 439B of NRS, which includes:

