41 Sec. 14. A health care entity or collection agency shall not engage in any of
42 the following actions to collect a medical debt:
43 1. Causing or threatening the arrest of a consumer, including, without
44 limitation, an arrest pursuant to NRS 31.470 to 31.730, inclusive;
45 2. Obtaining or threatening to obtain a lien against any real property of a
46 consumer which consists, in whole or in part, of the primary residence of the
47 consumer;
48 3. Foreclosing or threatening to foreclose on any real property of a
49 consumer which consists, in whole or in part, of the primary residence of the
50 consumer;
51 4. Garnishing or threatening to garnish any refund of federal income taxes
52 due to a consumer; or

